http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Campaign-to-promote-PDSU-State-conference/article14023910.ece

As part of the efforts to ensure active participation of students in the PDSU three-day State conference scheduled to be held in Warangal from January 29 to 31, the activists of PDSU conducted a campaign at SR&BGNR Government Arts and Science College by distributing pamphlets here on Wednesday. The student activists also conducted similar campaigns at the Government Junior College for Girls and some other educational institutions in the town to enlist the support of students to make the ensuing PDSU State conference a success.The activists highlighted the problems being faced by the student community and asserted that the grave challenges such as “privatisation” and “corporatisation” confronting higher education will be discussed threadbare during the upcoming conference.